Plain terms, so everyone understands:

1. FREE FOR NON-COMMERCIAL USE
   You may copy, use, modify, and share this software for free,
   as long as it is NOT for commercial purposes. Churches,
   parishes, schools, communities, and personal use are all
   welcome and encouraged.

2. WHAT COUNTS AS COMMERCIAL
   Commercial use means using this software (or a modified
   version of it) to make money — for example selling it,
   renting it, charging fees for a service built on it, or
   bundling it with a paid product. Voluntary donations to a
   church or community that uses this software are NOT
   considered commercial use.

3. COMMERCIAL USE NEEDS PERMISSION
   If you want to use this software commercially, ask the
   copyright holder first and get written permission.

4. KEEP THE CREDIT
   Keep this license file and the copyright notice in every
   copy or modified version you share.

5. SHARE-ALIKE
   If you share a modified version, share it under this same
   license.

6. NO WARRANTY
   This software is provided "as is", without warranty of any
   kind. The author is not liable for any damages arising from
   its use.

